Sharing a little family history... let me introduce you to my aunts father, Joaquin Garay.  He owned the famous “Copacabana” night club which opened in 1941.  A radio presenter and singer,  he was also known for being the voice of the rooster in Disney’s “The Three Caballeros”. Today marks the anniversary of his passing.  #fridaythe13th
Continued from my last post, “All Or Nothing”, completed in 2012.  #tbt #baroque #rococo @hasselblad @amatoofficial

All Or Nothing,” completed in 2012.  I’ve never shared this piece fully on Instagram for fear of losing the immense detail on such a small screen.  The original measures 60” and depicts a baroque interpretation of the female narcissus.  I spent weeks constructing the set and months of time spent on its creation. .

Pictured here is my piece “They Call Her Petunia,” the 8’ original print is currently on display as a part of my exhibit (and yes,  this piece inspired my song Petunia).
